commit.message:
gitlab markdown: Bug: handle empty classes

Empty classes are generated by fenced code blocks w/o the
`math` specifier, for example. Extend gitlab_markdown-sample.md to
include that case.

In particular, this fixes:

    $ pandoc -F gitlab_markdown.py gitlab_markdown-sample.md
    Traceback (most recent call last):
      File "./gitlab_markdown.py", line 26, in <module>
        toJSONFilter(gitlab_markdown)
      File "/path/to/pandocfilters/pandocfilters.py", line 132, in toJSONFilter
        toJSONFilters([action])
      File "/path/to/pandocfilters/pandocfilters.py", line 166, in toJSONFilters
        sys.stdout.write(applyJSONFilters(actions, source, format))
      File "/path/to/pandocfilters/pandocfilters.py", line 197, in applyJSONFilters
        altered = walk(altered, action, format, meta)
      File "/path/to/pandocfilters/pandocfilters.py", line 124, in walk
        x[k] = walk(x[k], action, format, meta)
      File "/path/to/pandocfilters/pandocfilters.py", line 111, in walk
        item['c'] if 'c' in item else None, format, meta)
      File "./gitlab_markdown.py", line 13, in gitlab_markdown
        if classes[0] == "math":
    IndexError: list index out of range
    Error running filter gitlab_markdown.py:
    Filter returned error status 1

gitlab markdown: Bug: add missing shebang

This is the only filter in examples/ which doesn't have it. However,
filter scripts need to be executable in order to be used with `pandoc -F
filter.py` or `pandoc -s -t json ... | filter.py | pandoc -f json`.

commit.message: LilyPond: take in account width and staffsize from metadata

Autodetect gregorio executables

Gregorio executable might have several names :

- gregorio for default executable in TeXLive ;
- gregorio-?_?_? for other versions available in the system.

This commit lets gabc.py autodetect those executables, instead of
hardcoding a list each time Gregorio is updated.
